Package: ODS4LDA
Type: Package
Title: Outcome Dependent Sampling (ODS) Designs for Linear Mixed Models Data Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person("Jonathan", "Schildcrout", email="jonny.schild@Vanderbilt.Edu",  role=c("aut", "cre")),
             person("Shawn",    "Garbett",     email="Shawn.Garbett@Vanderbilt.edu", role = c("ctb"))
            )
Author: Jonathan Schildcrout [aut, cre],
  Shawn Garbett [ctb]
Maintainer: Jonathan S. Schildcrout <jonathan.schildcrout@vanderbilt.edu>
Description: A package that fits linear mixed models under outcome dependent sampling (ODS)
  designs. At present, it uses maximum likelihood for random intercept and slope models
  for random sampling designs and ascertainment corrected maximum likelihood for
  ODS designs [see Schildcrout, J.S., Rathouz, P.J., Zelnick, L.R., Garbett, S.P., Heagerty, P.J..
  2015. "Biased Sampling Designs to Improve Research Efficiency: Factors Influencing
  Pulmonary Function over Time in Children with Asthma". Annual of Applied Statistics. (2):731-753. 
  <doi:10.1214/15-AOAS826>].
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Depends: mvtnorm, numDeriv
Suggests: testthat
